{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775893965475,"sessionID":"ses_284792a47ffeA58ANfk0D249zB","part":{"id":"prt_d7b8766a2001ru3dHNQ0BQMUdF","messageID":"msg_d7b875459001wRsYDYReRwp3FI","sessionID":"ses_284792a47ffeA58ANfk0D249zB","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-d9105c5097c8407198e7ae0efdbce48f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-037/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-037/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-037 — PCAP 分析器示例应用\n2: \n3: **Module:** example  \n4: **Language:** Python  \n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: A standalone PCAP analyzer example application demonstrating AgentCube sandbox orchestration with LangChain/LangGraph agents. This FastAPI service uploads PCAP files to an AgentCube sandbox, uses an LLM to plan and repair analysis scripts, executes them remotely, and generates structured analysis reports.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: FastAPI service bootstrap\n18: \n19: The system SHALL provide a FastAPI application that validates OpenAI-compatible API configuration at startup and builds ReAct agents for script planning and report generation.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Startup validates API key\n22: \n23: - **GIVEN** the FastAPI application is initializing\n24: - **WHEN** the startup event handler executes without a valid `OPENAI_API_KEY` environment variable\n25: - **THEN** the application SHALL raise `RuntimeError(\"OPENAI_API_KEY is required at startup\")` and SHALL NOT begin serving requests\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Startup builds LLM client\n28: \n29: - **GIVEN** a valid `OPENAI_API_KEY` is present\n30: - **WHEN** the startup event handler completes\n31: - **THEN** the application SHALL instantiate `ChatOpenAI` with `api_key`, `base_url` (from `OPENAI_API_BASE` defaulting to `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1`), and `model_name` (from `OPENAI_MODEL` defaulting to `Qwen/QwQ-32B`)\n32: \n33: ---\n34: \n35: ### Requirement: Analyze endpoint interface\n36: \n37: The system SHALL expose a `POST /analyze` endpoint accepting PCAP file uploads or local path references and returning structured analysis results.\n38: \n39: #### Scenario: Analyze with uploaded file\n40: \n41: - **GIVEN** a client sends `POST /analyze` with multipart `pcap_file` upload\n42: - **WHEN** the request reaches the handler\n43: - **THEN** the handler SHALL read the file bytes, stage them in the sandbox via `SandboxRunner.upload_bytes`, orchestrate analysis with retries, and return `AnalyzeResponse(script, results, report)`\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Analyze with local path\n46: \n47: - **GIVEN** a client sends `POST /analyze` with form field `pcap_path` pointing to a local file\n48: - **WHEN** the request reaches the handler\n49: - **THEN** the handler SHALL upload the file via `SandboxRunner.upload_file`, orchestrate analysis with retries, and return `AnalyzeResponse(script, results, report)`\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: Missing input validation\n52: \n53: - **GIVEN** a client sends `POST /analyze` without `pcap_file` and without `pcap_path`\n54: - **WHEN** the request reaches the handler\n55: - **THEN** the handler SHALL raise `HTTPException(status_code=400, detail=\"Either pcap_file or pcap_path required\")`\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ### Requirement: SandboxRunner orchestration\n60: \n61: The system SHALL implement `SandboxRunner` that wraps `CodeInterpreterClient` to upload files and execute shell commands in the remote sandbox.\n62: \n63: #### Scenario: SandboxRunner initialization\n64: \n65: - **GIVEN** `SandboxRunner(name=\"my-interpreter\", namespace=\"default\", warmup_sec=5)`\n66: - **WHEN** the runner is constructed\n67: - **THEN** it SHALL create a `CodeInterpreterClient` with `router_url` from `ROUTER_URL` env, `workload_manager_url` from `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env, `name`, `namespace`, and `ttl` derived from `warmup_sec`\n68: \n69: #### Scenario: SandboxRunner file upload\n70: \n71: - **GIVEN** a `SandboxRunner` instance with active session\n72: - **WHEN** `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)` or `upload_bytes(data, remote_path)` is called\n73: - **THEN** the runner SHALL delegate to `CodeInterpreterClient.upload_file` or write base64-encoded content via `write_file` respectively\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: SandboxRunner command execution\n76: \n77: - **GIVEN** a `SandboxRunner` instance with staged files\n78: - **WHEN** `run(command)` is invoked\n79: - **THEN** the runner SHALL call `execute_command(command)` and SHALL return a dict with `stdout`, `stderr`, `exit_code`\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: SandboxRunner cleanup\n82: \n83: - **GIVEN** a `SandboxRunner` that has completed analysis\n84: - **WHEN** `stop()` is called\n85: - **THEN** the runner SHALL call `CodeInterpreterClient.stop()` to delete the control-plane session and close HTTP connections\n86: \n87: ---\n88: \n89: ### Requirement: LLM agent orchestration\n90: \n91: The system SHALL use LangGraph ReAct agents for planning analysis scripts, repairing failed executions, and generating final reports.\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: Planner agent generates script\n94: \n95: - **GIVEN** the `PLANNER` ReAct agent built with `build_planner_agent(llm)`\n96: - **WHEN** `_plan_script(agent, pcap_path)` is called\n97: - **THEN** the agent SHALL receive a prompt describing the PCAP analysis task and SHALL return a Python script string for execution\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: Script execution with retry\n100: \n101: - **GIVEN** an initial script from the planner\n102: - **WHEN** `_execute_once_in_runner(runner, pcap_path, script)` returns non-zero `exit_code`\n103: - **THEN** `_analyze_with_retries` SHALL call `_repair_script(agent, prev_script, results)` to get a corrected script, and SHALL retry execution up to `max_retries` (default 2)\n104: \n105: #### Scenario: Reporter agent generates report\n106: \n107: - **GIVEN** successful execution results from `_execute_once_in_runner`\n108: - **WHEN** `_report(agent, results)` is called\n109: - **THEN** the `REPORTER` agent SHALL synthesize the execution outputs into a human-readable analysis report string\n110: \n111: ---\n112: \n113: ### Requirement: Configuration via environment\n114: \n115: The system SHALL read all runtime parameters from environment variables with documented defaults.\n116: \n117: #### Scenario: Default configuration values\n118: \n119: - **GIVEN** the application starts without custom environment overrides\n120: - **WHEN** globals are initialized\n121: - **THEN** `OPENAI_API_BASE` SHALL default to `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1`, `OPENAI_MODEL` to `Qwen/QwQ-32B`, `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME` to `my-interpreter`, `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE` to `default`, `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` to `5`\n122: \n123: #### Scenario: Server binding constants\n124: \n125: - **GIVEN** the FastAPI application\n126: - **WHEN** `uvicorn.run` is invoked in the main block\n127: - **THEN** it SHALL bind to `SERVER_HOST=\"0.0.0.0\"` and `SERVER_PORT=8000` with `SERVER_RELOAD=True` for development\n128: \n129: ---\n130: \n131: ### Requirement: Container image construction\n132: \n133: The system SHALL provide a Dockerfile that builds a minimal container with `uv`-managed dependencies and vendored SDK.\n134: \n135: #### Scenario: Dockerfile base and deps\n136: \n137: - **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile` build context\n138: - **WHEN** `docker build` runs\n139: - **THEN** the image SHALL use `ghcr.io/astral-sh/uv:python3.12-bookworm-slim` base, SHALL create a venv with `uv venv`, SHALL install `requirements.txt` packages with `uv pip install`, and SHALL copy `agentcube` SDK from `sdk-python/agentcube` to `/app/agentcube`\n140: \n141: #### Scenario: Dockerfile runtime config\n142: \n143: - **GIVEN** the built container image\n144: - **WHEN** the container starts\n145: - **THEN** `PYTHONPATH=\"/app\"` SHALL be set, port `8000` SHALL be exposed, and the default command SHALL be `[\"uv\", \"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]`\n146: \n147: ---\n148: \n149: ### Requirement: Kubernetes deployment manifest\n150: \n151: The system SHALL supply a Deployment manifest with resource constraints, secret mounting, and environment wiring.\n152: \n153: #### Scenario: Deployment resource limits\n154: \n155: - **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/deployment.yaml`\n156: - **WHEN** the manifest is applied to a Kubernetes cluster\n157: - **THEN** the container SHALL request `cpu: 200m` and `memory: 100Mi`, and SHALL limit to `cpu: 1` and `memory: 1Gi`\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: Secret mounting for API key\n160: \n161: - **GIVEN** the deployment container spec\n162: - **WHEN** the pod starts\n163: - **THEN** `OPENAI_API_KEY` SHALL be mounted from Secret `pcap-analyzer-secrets` key `openai-api-key`\n164: \n165: #### Scenario: Environment variables for AgentCube endpoints\n166: \n167: - **GIVEN** the deployment container spec\n168: - **WHEN** the pod starts\n169: - **THEN** environment variables `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL`, `OPENAI_API_BASE`, `OPENAI_MODEL`, `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME`, `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE`, and `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` SHALL be set with deployment-specific values\n170: \n171: #### Scenario: Container command matches local\n172: \n173: - **GIVEN** the deployment container spec\n174: - **WHEN** Kubernetes launches the container\n175: - **THEN** the command SHALL be `[\"uv\"]` with args `[\"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]`, identical to local Docker execution\n176: \n177: ---\n178: \n179: ### Requirement: Response schema\n180: \n181: The system SHALL define a Pydantic response model for the analyze endpoint.\n182: \n183: #### Scenario: AnalyzeResponse structure\n184: \n185: - **GIVEN** a successful analysis completion\n186: - **WHEN** the endpoint returns\n187: - **THEN** the response SHALL match `AnalyzeResponse` with fields `script: str`, `results: List[Dict[str, Any]]`, and `report: str`\n188: \n189: ---\n190: \n191: ### Requirement: Error handling patterns\n192: \n193: The system SHALL handle execution failures gracefully and surface meaningful errors to clients.\n194: \n195: #### Scenario: CommandExecutionError handling\n196: \n197: - **GIVEN** a sandbox command that returns non-zero exit code\n198: - **WHEN** `execute_command` raises `CommandExecutionError`\n199: - **THEN** the analysis loop SHALL capture the error, pass results to `_repair_script`, and retry if under the limit\n200: \n201: #### Scenario: Max retries exceeded\n202: \n203: - **GIVEN** script execution fails after `max_retries` attempts\n204: - **WHEN** the final repair attempt also fails\n205: - **THEN** the handler SHALL raise `HTTPException(status_code=500, detail=f\"Sandbox error: {e.stderr}\")`\n206: \n207: ---\n208: \n209: ## Constants Summary\n210: \n211: | Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n212: |----------|-------|------|---------|\n213: | `SERVER_HOST` | `\"0.0.0.0\"` | `pcap_analyzer.py` | HTTP bind address |\n214: | `SERVER_PORT` | `8000` | `pcap_analyzer.py` | HTTP listen port |\n215: | `SERVER_RELOAD` | `True` | `pcap_analyzer.py` | Development auto-reload |\n216: | `DEFAULT_API_BASE` | `\"https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1\"` | `pcap_analyzer.py` | OpenAI-compatible API base |\n217: | `DEFAULT_MODEL` | `\"Qwen/QwQ-32B\"` | `pcap_analyzer.py` | Default LLM model |\n218: | `DEFAULT_INTERPRETER_NAME` | `\"my-interpreter\"` | `pcap_analyzer.py` | Sandbox interpreter name |\n219: | `DEFAULT_NAMESPACE` | `\"default\"` | `pcap_analyzer.py` | Kubernetes namespace |\n220: | `DEFAULT_WARMUP_SEC` | `5` | `pcap_analyzer.py` | Sandbox warmup duration |\n221: | `MAX_RETRIES` | `2` | `pcap_analyzer.py` | Script repair retry limit |\n222: \n223: ---\n224: \n225: ## Dependencies Summary\n226: \n227: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n228: |---------|---------|---------|\n229: | `fastapi` | `0.120.0` | Web framework |\n230: | `uvicorn` | `0.38.0` | ASGI server |\n231: | `langchain` | `1.0.2` | LLM orchestration |\n232: | `langchain-openai` | `1.0.1` | OpenAI-compatible integration |\n233: | `langgraph` | `1.0.1` | Agent graph framework |\n234: | `langgraph-prebuilt` | `1.0.1` | Prebuilt ReAct agent pattern |\n235: | `python-multipart` | `0.0.20` | Form/file upload support |\n236: | `agentcube` | (vendored) | AgentCube SDK for sandbox |\n237: \n238: ---\n239: \n240: ## File Changes Summary\n241: \n242: | File | Action | Description |\n243: |------|--------|-------------|\n244: | `example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py` | create | FastAPI app with SandboxRunner, agents, /analyze endpoint |\n245: | `example/pcap-analyzer/requirements.txt` | create | LangChain, FastAPI, and supporting dependencies |\n246: | `example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile` | create | `uv`-based image with vendored SDK |\n247: | `example/pcap-analyzer/deployment.yaml` | create | K8s Deployment with Secret and env wiring |\n248: | `example/pcap-analyzer/README.md` | create | Usage and deployment documentation |\n249: \n250: ---\n251: \n252: ## References\n253: \n254: - python-sdk/design.md — AgentCube SDK design\n255: - python-sdk/spec.md — AgentCube SDK specification\n256: - integrations/design.md — Extended integrations architecture\n257: - integrations/spec.md — PCAP analyzer requirements (shared)\n258: \n259: ---\n260: \n261: ## Validation Checklist\n262: \n263: - [ ] Application fails startup without `OPENAI_API_KEY`\n264: - [ ] `POST /analyze` accepts `pcap_file` upload\n265: - [ ] `POST /analyze` accepts `pcap_path` form field\n266: - [ ] `POST /analyze` returns 400 when neither input provided\n267: - [ ] `SandboxRunner` wraps `CodeInterpreterClient` correctly\n268: - [ ] `SandboxRunner.upload_file` stages files in sandbox\n269: - [ ] `SandboxRunner.run` executes commands and returns structured output\n270: - [ ] `SandboxRunner.stop` cleans up sessions\n271: - [ ] PLANNER agent generates executable Python scripts\n272: - [ ] `_analyze_with_retries` retries on execution failure\n273: - [ ] REPORTER agent synthesizes results into report\n274: - [ ] Environment defaults match constants\n275: - [ ] Dockerfile uses `uv` and vendors SDK\n276: - [ ] Deployment manifest sets resources and secrets correctly\n277: - [ ] `AnalyzeResponse` schema matches endpoint output\n\n(End of file - total 277 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-037 — PCAP 分析器示例应用\n\n**Module:** example  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nA standalone PCAP analyzer example application demonstrating AgentCube sandbox orchestration with LangChain/LangGraph agents. This FastAPI service uploads PCAP files to an AgentCube sandbox, uses an LLM to plan and repair analysis scripts, executes them remotely, and generates structured analysis reports.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: FastAPI service bootstrap\n\nThe system SHALL provide a FastAPI application that validates OpenAI-compatible API configuration at startup and builds ReAct agents for script planning and report generation.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-037/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775893965459,"end":1775893965473}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775893965478,"sessionID":"ses_284792a47ffeA58ANfk0D249zB","part":{"id":"prt_d7b876a75001JOCiablzkbcQGT","messageID":"msg_d7b875459001wRsYDYReRwp3FI","sessionID":"ses_284792a47ffeA58ANfk0D249zB","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-2f102374b1d444849d78470775874578","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-037/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-037/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-037 — PCAP 分析器示例应用\n2: \n3: ## 概述\n4: \n5: | 属性 | 值 |\n6: |------|-----|\n7: | AR | AR-037 |\n8: | Module | example |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## 1. Purpose (目的)\n15: \n16: 创建一个完整的 PCAP（网络包捕获）分析器示例应用，演示 AgentCube Python SDK 的 `CodeInterpreterClient` 在真实场景中的使用方式。该示例展示：\n17: \n18: 1. **文件上传**: 将 PCAP 文件上传到沙箱环境\n19: 2. **代码执行**: 在隔离环境中运行 Python 分析脚本（使用 dpkt/scapy 等库）\n20: 3. **结果提取**: 从沙箱下载分析结果文件\n21: 4. **会话生命周期管理**: 完整的上下文管理器使用模式\n22: \n23: 此示例作为 SDK 文档的核心演示案例，帮助用户理解如何将 AgentCube 用于需要安全执行环境的网络分析任务。\n24: \n25: ---\n26: \n27: ## 2. Scope (范围)\n28: \n29: ### 2.1 In Scope\n30: \n31: | Deliverable | Description |\n32: |-------------|-------------|\n33: | `sdk-python/examples/pcap_analyzer.py` | 主示例脚本，演示完整 PCAP 分析流程 |\n34: | `sdk-python/examples/sample_pcap.pcapng` | 示例 PCAP 文件用于测试（小规模，约 50KB） |\n35: | `sdk-python/examples/analyze_pcap.py` | 分析脚本模板，上传到沙箱执行 |\n36: \n37: ### 2.2 功能清单\n38: \n39: | 功能 | 实现方式 |\n40: |------|----------|\n41: | PCAP 文件上传 | `CodeInterpreterClient.upload_file()` |\n42: | 分析脚本上传 | `CodeInterpreterClient.write_file()` |\n43: | 分析执行 | `CodeInterpreterClient.run_code()` 或 `execute_command()` |\n44: | 结果下载 | `CodeInterpreterClient.download_file()` |\n45: | 会话管理 | Context manager (`with` 语句) |\n46: | 错误处理 | `CommandExecutionError` 异常捕获 |\n47: \n48: ### 2.3 Out of Scope\n49: \n50: | Item | Reason |\n51: |------|--------|\n52: | 复杂的网络协议解析 | 示例仅演示基础统计（包数、协议分布） |\n53: | PCAP 文件生成 | 使用现有示例文件或用户自行提供 |\n54: | 可视化输出 | 示例输出为文本/JSON，不生成图表 |\n55: | 实时流分析 | 仅支持静态 PCAP 文件分析 |\n56: | GUI/Web 界面 | CLI 示例，不包含可视化前端 |\n57: \n58: ---\n59: \n60: ## 3. Impact Analysis (影响分析)\n61: \n62: ### 3.1 新增文件\n63: \n64: | File | Description |\n65: |------|-------------|\n66: | `sdk-python/examples/pcap_analyzer.py` | 主示例脚本 (~120 行) |\n67: | `sdk-python/examples/sample_pcap.pcapng` | 示例 PCAP 文件 (~50KB) |\n68: | `sdk-python/examples/analyze_pcap.py` | 分析脚本模板 (~30 行) |\n69: \n70: ### 3.2 修改文件\n71: \n72: | File | Change |\n73: |------|--------|\n74: | None | 本次 AR 仅新增示例文件，不修改现有模块 |\n75: \n76: ### 3.3 Upstream Dependencies\n77: \n78: | Dependency | Purpose |\n79: |------------|---------|\n80: | `agentcube-sdk` | SDK 核心库 |\n81: | `dpkt` (可选) | PCAP 解析库，示例分析脚本中使用 |\n82: | `scapy` (可选) | 替代 PCAP 解析方案，演示用户可选依赖 |\n83: \n84: ### 3.4 Downstream Consumers\n85: \n86: | Consumer | Usage |\n87: |----------|-------|\n88: | SDK 文档 | 作为官方示例嵌入文档 |\n89: | 新用户 | 学习 SDK 使用模式的参考 |\n90: | 集成测试 | 可扩展为 E2E 测试场景 |\n91: \n92: ---\n93: \n94: ## 4. Alternatives Considered (备选方案)\n95: \n96: ### Alternative 1: 内联分析代码\n97: \n98: **Approach**: 将分析逻辑直接嵌入 `pcap_analyzer.py`，通过 `run_code()` 执行。\n99: \n100: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n101: |--------|------------|\n102: | Pros | 单文件简单结构，无需额外脚本文件 |\n103: | Cons | 长代码串传递不便，难以复用，调试困难 |\n104: \n105: **Decision**: 混合采用。简单统计内联，复杂分析分离为脚本文件上传。\n106: \n107: ### Alternative 2: 使用 scapy 替代 dpkt\n108: \n109: **Approach**: 分析脚本使用 scapy 库解析 PCAP。\n110: \n111: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n112: |--------|------------|\n113: | Pros | 功能更强大，支持更多协议 |\n114: | Cons | 依赖更大（scapy ~5MB），沙箱环境需预装 |\n115: \n116: **Decision**: 示例提供两种分析脚本模板（dpkt 轻量版和 scapy 功能版），用户按需选择。\n117: \n118: ### Alternative 3: AgentRuntimeClient 替代\n119: \n120: **Approach**: 使用 `AgentRuntimeClient` 调用已部署的 PCAP 分析 Agent。\n121: \n122: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n123: |--------|------------|\n124: | Pros | 更符合 Agent 架构，可复用分析服务 |\n125: | Cons | 需要先部署 Agent Runtime，示例复杂度增加 |\n126: \n127: **Decision**: 作为后续 AR 考虑。当前 AR-037 专注演示 `CodeInterpreterClient`。\n128: \n129: ### Alternative 4: 不提供示例 PCAP 文件\n130: \n131: **Approach**: 用户自行提供 PCAP 文件，示例仅提供分析脚本。\n132: \n133: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n134: |--------|------------|\n135: | Pros | 减少仓库体积，避免生成测试数据 |\n136: | Cons | 用户无法直接运行示例，体验不完整 |\n137: \n138: **Decision**: 提供小型示例 PCAP 文件（~50KB，约 100 个包），确保可一键运行。\n139: \n140: ---\n141: \n142: ## 5. Risks\n143: \n144: | Risk | Mitigation |\n145: |------|------------|\n146: | 沙箱环境缺少 PCAP 解析库 | 分析脚本内嵌 dpkt 纯 Python 实现，或用户提供依赖安装命令 |\n147: | PCAP 文件过大导致上传慢 | 示例文件控制在 50KB 以内；用户大文件建议分批处理 |\n148: | 分析超时（复杂协议） | 设置合理 timeout 默认值 (60s)；示例仅做基础统计 |\n149: | 示例文件版权问题 | 使用公开网络测试数据或自制模拟数据 |\n150: \n151: ---\n152: \n153: ## 6. Implementation Checklist\n154: \n155: - [ ] 创建 `sdk-python/examples/pcap_analyzer.py` 主脚本\n156: - [ ] 实现 PCAP 上传 → 分析 → 结果下载完整流程\n157: - [ ] 添加 CLI 参数解析（router-url, pcap-path, output-path）\n158: - [ ] 创建 `sdk-python/examples/analyze_pcap.py` 分析脚本模板\n159: - [ ] 生成或获取小型示例 PCAP 文件 `sample_pcap.pcapng`\n160: - [ ] 添加错误处理示例（捕获 `CommandExecutionError`）\n161: - [ ] 编写脚本头部文档说明使用方法\n162: - [ ] 手动测试示例运行（需有 Router/WorkloadManager 环境）\n163: \n164: ---\n165: \n166: ## 7. References\n167: \n168: - python-sdk/design.md — SDK 设计文档\n169: - python-sdk/spec.md — SDK 规范\n170: - `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` — CodeInterpreterClient 实现\n171: - `sdk-python/examples/agent_runtime_usage.py` — 已有示例参考\n172: - dpkt 文档: https://dpkt.readthedocs.io/\n173: - scapy 文档: https://scapy.readthedocs.io/\n\n(End of file - total 173 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-037 — PCAP 分析器示例应用\n\n## 概述\n\n| 属性 | 值 |\n|------|-----|\n| AR | AR-037 |\n| Module | example |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose (目的)\n\n创建一个完整的 PCAP（网络包捕获）分析器示例应用，演示 AgentCube Python SDK 的 `CodeInterpreterClient` 在真实场景中的使用方式。该示例展示：\n\n1. **文件上传**: 将 PCAP 文件上传到沙箱环境\n2. **代码执行**: 在隔离环境中运行 Python 分析脚本（使用 dpkt/scapy 等库）\n3. **结果提取**: 从沙箱下载分析结果文件","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-037/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775893965462,"end":1775893965476}}}}
